{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013sG6ZhJqQQiaTbK2DvhoA6","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me compile the final report with all findings:\n\n## Search Results: MongoDB Certificate Rotation and TLS\n\nI found **2 case directories** related to certificate/TLS rotation in `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/`:\n\n### 1. **Certificate Rotation Case**\n**Path:** `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/test.yaml` - Main test definition\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/statefulset.yaml` - MongoDB StatefulSet with TLS volume mounts\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/services.yaml` - Kubernetes headless service\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/resource/openssl-toolbox.yaml` - Helper pod for certificate generation\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/certificate-rotation/oracle/oracle.py` - Verification oracle script\n\n**Key Parameters (from test.yaml):**\n- `tls_ca_secret_name`: defaults to **`mongodb-tls-ca`** (holds CA cert and key)\n- `tls_cert_secret_name`: defaults to **`mongodb-tls-cert`** (holds server certificate bundle)\n- `old_tls_configmap_name`: defaults to `mongodb-tls-old` (stores fingerprints of pre-rotation certs)\n- `old_cert_valid_days`: defaults to 2 days\n\n**Task Description:** Rotate server certificates without downtime while keeping CA trust unchanged and ensuring new certificates valid for ~1 year.\n\n**Secret References in StatefulSet:**\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - name: mongo-tls-cert\n    secret:\n      secretName: mongodb-tls-cert\n  - name: mongo-tls-ca\n    secret:\n      secretName: mongodb-tls-ca\n```\n\n**Mounted Paths in MongoDB container:**\n- `/etc/mongo-cert/server.pem` (from `mongodb-tls-cert` secret)\n- `/etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt` (from `mongodb-tls-ca` secret)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **TLS Setup Case**\n**Path:** `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/`\n\n**Files:**\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/test.yaml` - Main test definition\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/resource/statefulset.yaml` - Basic MongoDB StatefulSet (no TLS pre-configured)\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/resource/services.yaml` - Kubernetes headless service\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/resource/openssl-toolbox.yaml` - OpenSSL helper pod\n- `/Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/tls-setup/oracle/oracle.py` - Verification oracle script\n\n**Task Description:** Enable TLS for a running MongoDB replica set (from plain to TLS-required mode).\n\n**Certificate Files Expected to be Mounted:**\n- `/etc/tls/ca.crt`\n- `/etc/tls/server.pem`\n- `/etc/tls/client.pem` (for mutual TLS)\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n1. **Secret Names with `mongodb-tls-*` prefix:** Both defined in the certificate-rotation case\n   - `mongodb-tls-ca` - Stores CA certificate and key\n   - `mongodb-tls-cert` - Stores server certificate bundle (server.pem)\n\n2. **Secrets are created dynamically:** The certificate-rotation case's test.yaml shows secrets are created via `kubectl create secret generic` commands in the precondition unit (lines 97-103), not pre-defined YAML files.\n\n3. **No Static Secret YAML Files:** The certificate-rotation case does NOT include `secrets.yaml` in its resource directory. Secrets are generated on-the-fly during test preconditions using OpenSSL certificate generation.\n\n4. **Other Cases with Secret Files:** Other MongoDB cases (password-rotation, custom-roles, mongod-config-update) DO have `secrets.yaml` files, but the certificate-rotation case uses dynamic secret generation instead."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0656db3c-c9d4-4a0b-8d45-5c2a815a427e","uuid":"6f4337d0-a954-4de3-b8b1-4111b0c4b0a8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T11:33:04.106Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search in /Users/leo/Karma/cases/mongodb/ for any case directory o