{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WZp4YQYPvMpV9K9DjoaKAX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so we have 3 replicas (the precondition for tls-setup probably reset to 3). The tls-setup case's precondition deleted the namespace and recreated everything from scratch. Let me verify by looking at the tls-setup oracle/evidence to see what happened.\n\nNow let me proceed with the implementation:\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Use openssl-toolbox to generate new CA + old server cert (2d) + new server cert (365d)\n2. Create `mongodb-tls-ca` secret (with ca.crt + ca.key)\n3. Create `mongodb-tls-old` configmap (with fingerprints)\n4. Create `mongodb-tls-cert` secret (with new server cert, 365d)\n5. Update StatefulSet to use new secrets and mount paths\n6. Wait for rolling restart to complete\n7. Wait for replica set to reform\n\nI'll execute the openssl operations in the openssl-toolbox pod, then update the StatefulSet. Since we're changing the CA entirely, the rolling restart will cause TLS verification failures between old-CA and new-CA nodes, so I need to think through the transition carefully to minimize downtime. old CA → TLS handshake fails. Once all nodes update to the new CA and cert, the replica set should reform. MongoDB's election process means that with 3 members, if one node is temporarily unreachable due to cert verification issues, the other two can maintain quorum and elect a primary, so the cluster can survive the rolling restart.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider the transition window more carefully. When mongo-rs-2 updates first but the others haven't yet, it becomes isolated since it's the only node using the new CA, leaving mongo-rs-0 and mongo-rs-1 able to communicate with each other and maintain quorum.\n\nThen when mongo-rs-1 updates, it joins mongo-rs-2 on the new CA, potentially triggering an election since they can now form a quorum together while mongo-rs-0 is left isolated on the old CA. Finally, once mongo-rs-0 updates, all three nodes can communicate again and the replica set is fully healthy.\n\nNow I need to implement this. I'm deciding between using `kubectl patch` to update the StatefulSet volumes and command, or applying the full resource definition directly. The key question is whether the volumes in the target StatefulSet are fundamentally different or just updated references to the new CA secret. readOnly: true}, {mountPath: /etc/mongo-ca, name: mongo-tls-ca, readOnly: true}]` and command flags pointing to `/etc/mongo-cert/server.pem`, `/etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt`, and allowing connections without certificates.\n\nI'm realizing the volumes and mounts are different enough that I can't just patch them directly since StatefulSets don't allow direct updates to those fields. But actually, `kubectl apply` should update the pod template spec and trigger a rolling update. Let me check what the case's StatefulSet YAML specifies exactly.\n\nMy plan is to generate the certificates on the openssl-toolbox pod, create the necessary secrets and configmap, apply the case's StatefulSet YAML, and wait for the rollout to complete. For the certificate SANs, I need to include localhost, mongo, and the various DNS names for the StatefulSet pods across the cluster.\n\nNow I'll write out the kubectl commands to execute this step by step.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5529,"cache_read_input_tokens":54017,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5529},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0656db3c-c9d4-4a0b-8d45-5c2a815a427e","uuid":"18e3b466-5b94-4702-b25c-c6ae675efb20","request_id":"req_011Cc4ykA2RDwnVBULMvSywY"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WZp4YQYPvMpV9K9DjoaKAX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture of what's needed. The current MongoDB uses the `mongo-tls` secret (from stage_04 tls-setup), but the certificate-rotation oracle expects `mongodb-tls-ca`, `mongodb-tls-cert`, and `mongodb-tls-old` secrets/configmap with the new StatefulSet structure. I'll:\n\n1. Generate a new CA + \"old\" server cert (2 days) + new server cert (365 days) on the openssl-toolbox\n2. Create the expected K8s resources\n3. Update the StatefulSet to the new mount structure\n4. Wait for the rolling restart and replica set to reform\n\n**Step 1: Generate all certificates on openssl-toolbox**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5529,"cache_read_input_tokens":54017,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5529},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0656db3c-c9d4-4a0b-8d45-5c2a815a427e","uuid":"5722c717-5f55-4bad-9320-30ce11f144b1","request_id":"req_011Cc4ykA2RDwnVBULMvSywY"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WZp4YQYPvMpV9K9DjoaKAX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011B8QdSgDuFMLzrbYYBZYX3","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n mongodb exec openssl-toolbox -- /bin/sh -c '\nset -e\nmkdir -p /tmp/newcerts\n\ncat > /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf << \"EOFCNF\"\n[req]\ndistinguished_name=req_distinguished_name\nreq_extensions=v3_req\nprompt=no\n[req_distinguished_name]\nCN=mongo-rs\n[v3_req]\nkeyUsage=critical,digitalSignature,keyEncipherment\nextendedKeyUsage=serverAuth,clientAuth\nsubjectAltName=@alt_names\n[alt_names]\nDNS.1=localhost\nDNS.2=mongo\nDNS.3=mongo.mongodb\nDNS.4=mongo.mongodb.svc\nDNS.5=mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.6=mongo-rs-0.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.7=mongo-rs-1.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nDNS.8=mongo-rs-2.mongo.mongodb.svc.cluster.local\nIP.1=127.0.0.1\nEOFCNF\n\n# New CA\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/newcerts/ca.key 2048\nopenssl req -x509 -new -nodes -key /tmp/newcerts/ca.key -sha256 -days 3650 \\\n  -subj \"/CN=mongo-ca\" -out /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt\n\n# \"Old\" server cert (2 days) - pre-rotation fingerprint\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/newcerts/old-server.key 2048\nopenssl req -new -key /tmp/newcerts/old-server.key -out /tmp/newcerts/old-server.csr \\\n  -config /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf\nopenssl x509 -req -in /tmp/newcerts/old-server.csr -CA /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt \\\n  -CAkey /tmp/newcerts/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out /tmp/newcerts/old-server.crt \\\n  -days 2 -extensions v3_req -extfile /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf\ncat /tmp/newcerts/old-server.crt /tmp/newcerts/old-server.key > /tmp/newcerts/old-server.pem\n\n# New server cert (365 days) - post-rotation\nopenssl genrsa -out /tmp/newcerts/server.key 2048\nopenssl req -new -key /tmp/newcerts/server.key -out /tmp/newcerts/server.csr \\\n  -config /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf\nopenssl x509 -req -in /tmp/newcerts/server.csr -CA /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt \\\n  -CAkey /tmp/newcerts/ca.key -CAcreateserial -out /tmp/newcerts/server.crt \\\n  -days 365 -extensions v3_req -extfile /tmp/newcerts/openssl.cnf\ncat /tmp/newcerts/server.crt /tmp/newcerts/server.key > /tmp/newcerts/server.pem\n\necho \"=== CA fingerprint ===\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in /tmp/newcerts/ca.crt\necho \"=== Old server fingerprint ===\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in /tmp/newcerts/old-server.crt\necho \"=== New server fingerprint ===\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in /tmp/newcerts/server.crt\necho \"=== New server validity ===\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -dates -in /tmp/newcerts/server.crt\necho \"DONE\"\n'\n","description":"Generate new CA, old server cert (2d), and new server cert (365d) in openssl-toolbox"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5529,"cache_read_input_tokens":54017,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5529},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0656db3c-c9d4-4a0b-8d45-5c2a815a427e","uuid":"79aef2e1-7457-4a84-bd24-5681e0b20699","request_id":"req_011Cc4ykA2RDwnVBULMvSywY"}
